
[1]indicative

   INDIC'ATIVE,a. [L. indicativus.] Showing; giving intimation or
   knowledge of something not visible or obvious. Reserve is not always
   indicative of modesty; it may be indicative of prudence.

   1. In grammar, the indicative mode is the form of the verb that
   indicates,that is, which affirms or denies; as, he writes, he is
   writing; they run; we misimprove advantages. It also asks questions;
   as, has the mail arrived?
